	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Durban - A 21-year-old man appeared in the Hammarsdale
Magistrate's Court on Monday for allegedly killing a policeman, the Hawks said. Mthokozisi Phakathi was off-duty when he was shot twice
last Tuesday, Lieutenant Simphiwe Mhlongo said. Siyabonga Shabalala was arrested on Friday and charged
with murder. The case was postponed to May 30 for a bail application. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  